item.title: Netanyahu vows to extract 'heavy price' for missile attack by Houthi rebels
item.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has vowed to retaliate against Yemen's Houthi rebels after they successfully launched a hypersonic ballistic missile into central Israel. The missile traveled over 2,000 kilometers before fragmenting in midair, causing no injuries. This is the first time Houthis have reached central Israel with their attacks.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 34 Iran women prisoners on hunger strike: Jailed Nobel peace laureate
item.description: On September 15, 2024, thirty-four female political prisoners in Iran's Evin Prison started a hunger strike to mark two years since the 'Woman, Life, Freedom' movement and Mahsa Amini's death. The protest aims to oppose government oppression and show solidarity with the Iranian people.

item.title: Trump's 'mass deportation' threat evokes images of WW2 internment camps
item.description: A misleading social media post in Springfield, Ohio claimed Haitians were eating pet cats, leading to threats and rumors. City officials have found no credible evidence supporting these claims. Nevertheless, Donald Trump has announced plans for mass deportations of Haitian immigrants, stirring unrest and excitement among his radical followers.
item.dc:creator: Chidanand Rajghatta

item.title: Teen accused of killing groom just before wedding gets caught at Canadian border
item.description: A 17-year-old from Long Island was arrested at the Canadian border following a fatal hit-and-run in Harlem that killed a groom just hours before his wedding. The teenager faces charges in Manhattan Criminal Court, with his attorney claiming the case is weak and pointing out his client's health issues including autism and epilepsy.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Rising floodwaters trigger evacuations in Czech Republic and Poland
item.description: Severe flooding has struck Central Europe due to torrential rains, heavily impacting the Czech Republic. Authorities declared top-level flood warnings across nearly 90 locations, prompting mass evacuations and widespread power outages. The situation remains critical in Poland and Austria, where fatalities have been reported. Meteorologists caution that conditions could deteriorate further with more heavy rainfall expected.

item.title: 'US ready to turn page on politics of division, hate': Harris takes jibe at Trump, says 'baton is in our hands'
item.description: At the Congressional Black Caucusâ€™s Phoenix Awards dinner, Vice President Kamala Harris contrasted her administration's agenda with former President Trump's, focusing on healthcare and economic opportunity. President Joe Biden emphasized his commitment to unity and rebuilding the middle class while condemning divisive actions like the January 6 insurrection and attacks on affirmative action.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Imran Khan comprares Pakistan's ruling dispensation with Yahya Khan's era, says 'no point' in calling Shehbaz Sharif PM
item.description: Imran Khan, the imprisoned former prime minister of Pakistan, has drawn parallels between the current political environment and the era of military ruler Yahya Khan. He criticized the ruling coalition and institutions for corruption and lack of rule of law. Khan also highlighted poor economic conditions and urged for more foreign investment in Pakistan.

item.title: Massachusetts state police recruit dies during boxing training exercise
item.description: Enrique Delgado-Garcia, a 25-year-old Massachusetts state police recruit, died after becoming unresponsive during a defensive tactics exercise at the academy. Despite quick medical intervention and hospitalization, he did not survive. An investigation is ongoing, and Delgado-Garcia will receive full state police honors for his service.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Won't give California wildfire aid if governor doesnâ€™t change water policy: Donald Trump
item.description: Donald Trump has threatened to withhold federal aid for battling California wildfires unless Governor Gavin Newsom changes a policy that protects the endangered smelt fish. Trump criticized Newsom and promised ample water for farmers if reelected, while also linking various state issues to Vice President Kamala Harris's previous roles in California.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Does Googleâ€™s milliseconds ad constitute an illegal monopoly?
item.description: A federal court in Virginia is currently evaluating whether Google's ad tech stack constitutes an illegal monopoly. The justice department and several states claim that Google's dominance has negatively impacted publishers and advertisers. Google argues its innovations have enhanced ad quality, but the government accuses it of manipulating ad sales auctions to benefit itself.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Tropical Storm Ileana makes landfall on Mexico's Sinaloa coast after pounding Los Cabos
item.description: Tropical Storm Ileana made landfall in Sinaloa, Mexico, after hitting Los Cabos with winds of 40 mph. The storm reached near Topolobampo and is expected to weaken into a tropical depression over the Gulf of California. Authorities prepared shelters and suspended classes to ensure safety in affected areas.

item.title: Is North Korea's nuclear threat growing? New photos raise alarm
item.description: North Korea released images of its uranium enrichment facility, suggesting several undisclosed nuclear sites. The photos likely show the Kangson site with Kim Jong Un inspecting centrifuges. Analysts note possible expansions at Yongbyon and Kangson, indicating progress in North Korea's uranium enrichment efforts to enhance its nuclear arsenal.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Invasion of my privacy': Former first lady Melania Trump slams FBIâ€™s Mar-a-Lago raid, says 'warning to all Americans'
item.description: Melania Trump criticized the FBI's 2022 raid on Mar-a-Lago as an invasion of privacy and a warning to all Americans about respecting freedom and rights. The raid recovered over 100 classified documents. Her upcoming memoir, set for release on October 1, will provide more details.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Egypt train collision: Two passenger trains collide; three dead, 49 injured
item.description: A train collision in Zagazig, northeast of Cairo, killed three people, including two children, and injured 49 others. Five of the injured are critically hurt. Rescue operations continue as emergency responders assist those affected. This incident underscores persistent challenges within Egypt's railway system despite government promises for improvements.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: ABC moderator Linsey Davis admits to fact-checking Trump due to concerns raised in CNN debate
item.description: ABC News anchor Linsey Davis faced criticism for repeatedly fact-checking Donald Trump during a recent US presidential debate while not challenging Kamala Harris. Davis explained that her decision was influenced by concerns from a previous CNN debate. Despite backlash, she defended her approach, acknowledging the difficulty in catching every incorrect statement.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Typhoon Yagi claims 350 lives, 74 in Myanmar; 89 missing
item.description: Typhoon Yagi's impact on Myanmar has led to a death toll of 74, with nearly 350 lives lost across Southeast Asia. At least 89 people are missing. Floods and landslides have displaced approximately 240,000 people in Myanmar. In a rare move, the junta has requested international aid amid ongoing conflict since the military coup in 2021.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Mother sells Taylor Swift's concert tickets after singer endorses Kamala Harris, netizens react
item.description: Taylor Swift endorsed Kamala Harris, leading to varied reactions. A mother sold concert tickets due to Swift's political views, criticizing her non-Christian beliefs and supporting Donald Trump. The endorsement increased traffic to vote.gov, demonstrating Swift's strong influence on young voters.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 6 foreigners arrested over alleged plan to destabilise Venezuela by attacking President Nicolas Maduro, says government
item.description: Venezuelan authorities have detained six individuals, including three Americans, over allegations of plotting an attack on President Nicolas Maduro. This development comes amid rising tensions with the US and Spain after a contested presidential election. Officials claim the suspects were involved in planning terrorist activities and have confiscated a large cache of weapons.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Comoros president's attacker found dead in prison cell, investigation underway
item.description: A soldier who attacked Comoros President Azali Assoumani with a knife during a funeral was found dead in his prison cell under unclear circumstances. Authorities are investigating both the motive behind the attack and the cause of his death. The president sustained minor injuries but is out of danger.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Salvagers launch new attempt to tow an oil tanker blown up by Yemen's Houthi rebels
item.description: Salvage operations have started for the Greek-flagged oil tanker Sounion, which is burning in the Red Sea after being attacked by Yemen's Houthi rebels. The EU's Operation Aspides is providing security for tugboats involved in the effort. The tanker holds 1 million barrels of crude oil, heightening concerns about an environmental disaster.
